# --- credential-shaped stray files (the FILENAME is the secret) -------------------
# A stray shell redirect (e.g. `cmd > "$TOKEN"`) can create a file whose NAME is a
# live-shaped Anthropic OAuth token (sk-ant-oat01-...). The 46-byte content is
# innocuous (a path), but the token-shaped filename would be written into git
# history by any `git add -A`. Never stage it. (Rotate the token + delete the file
# is an operator action — this rule only stops the leak vector.)
sk-ant-*
sk-ant-oat01-*

# --- runtime demo artifact (regenerated on every run) -----------------------------
# cmd/memqdemo writes memqdemo-report.json into its working dir on each run as the
# machine-readable witness of that run; it is a build product, not source. Track the
# code that emits it, not the emission.
memqdemo-report.json

